    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{4}{t^{2}-12t+20}-\frac{t-6}{t^{2}-12t+20}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{t-2}, t\ne 10</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{4}{t^{2}-12t+20}-\frac{t-6}{t^{2}-12t+20}} 
      \amp = \frac{{4-\left(t-6\right)}}{{t^{2}-12t+20}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{4-t+6}}{{\left(t-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-2\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-t+10}}{{\left(t-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-2\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-\left(t-10\right)}}{{\left(t-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{t-2}, t\ne 10}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t-10</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {10}</m>.</p>
</solution>
